<div class="page-header"><h1>Your student's tuition drops the day this passes</h1>
<p>In-district status at ACC means immediate savings for every PfISD family with a current or future ACC student. The numbers are straightforward.</p></div>
<div class="prose">

<h2>The tuition savings</h2>
<p>ACC in-district tuition and fees: $85 per credit hour. Out-of-district (what Pflugerville pays now): $286 per credit hour. Savings per credit hour: $201. ACC has not raised in-district tuition or general fees in 12 consecutive years.</p>
<table class="compare-table">
<thead><tr><th>Enrollment</th><th>Credits</th><th>In-district</th><th>Out-of-district</th><th>You save</th></tr></thead>
<tbody>
<tr><td>2 classes, 1 semester</td><td>6</td><td class="highlight">$510</td><td>$1,716</td><td class="savings">$1,206</td></tr>
<tr><td>Full-time, 1 semester</td><td>15</td><td class="highlight">$1,275</td><td>$4,290</td><td class="savings">$3,015</td></tr>
<tr><td>Full-time, 1 year</td><td>30</td><td class="highlight">$2,550</td><td>$8,580</td><td class="savings">$6,030</td></tr>
<tr><td>Associate degree (2 years)</td><td>60</td><td class="highlight">$5,100</td><td>$17,160</td><td class="savings">$12,060</td></tr>
</tbody>
</table>

<h2>What free tuition actually means for PfISD students</h2>
<p>ACC's free tuition pilot (launched 2024) eliminates tuition and general fees for recent high school graduates and GED completers in the ACC service area. PfISD is in the service area, so PfISD grads qualify. The catch: out-of-district students still pay the $201 per credit hour out-of-district fee, even under the free tuition program.</p>
<div class="callout"><strong>The penalty is real:</strong> A PfISD free-tuition student taking 15 credits per semester pays $3,015 in out-of-district fees. A Round Rock or Leander student taking the same courses pays $0. Over three years of free tuition eligibility (90 credits), a PfISD student pays $18,090 that an in-district student does not. Source: <a href="https://catalog.austincc.edu/college-entry/paying-for-college/acc-free-tuition-pilot-program/" target="_blank">ACC Free Tuition Pilot</a>.</div>
<p>If Pflugerville joins the ACC district, that $18,090 penalty disappears.</p>

<h2>Dual credit and Career Academies</h2>
<p>PfISD already runs an ACC dual credit partnership and Career Academies in accounting, automotive, construction, advanced manufacturing, and culinary arts. ACC eliminated the out-of-district fee for dual credit students in Spring 2024, so current high school students are not paying the differential. But when they graduate and continue at ACC, they re-enter as out-of-district and pay $286/credit hour unless the annexation passes. Source: <a href="https://www.pfisd.net/programs/counseling/acc-dual-credit-partnership" target="_blank">PfISD Dual Credit</a>, <a href="https://dualcredit.austincc.edu/costs/" target="_blank">ACC Dual Credit Costs</a>.</p>
<p>In-district status creates a seamless, affordable pathway: dual credit in high school, then continued enrollment at ACC at the same low rate.</p>

