<h2>First-generation families</h2>
<p>ACC has an open admissions policy. No entrance exams, GPA minimums, or admission competition. In-district tuition is $85 per credit hour. Financial aid, including Pell Grants and ACC scholarships, is available and can be applied on top of in-district rates. 27% of ACC students receive grants or scholarships, with an average aid amount of $7,158. For families navigating the college system for the first time, ACC is designed to be the accessible starting point.</p>
